ns2:PrimaryTypeDefinition.ns1:desc: This Managed Object contains a UTRAN cell for TDD (Time Division Duplex).

ns2:primaryTypeAttribute.ns1:desc: The Location Area Code of the external UTRAN cell. A fixed-length code identifying the location area within a PLMN. Refer to 3GPP TS 23.003. The value 0 of the attribute is used to mark invalid/unusable lac information for the cell. For example, handover to an external UTRAN cell (that is part of a Utran cell relation) can be considered only if the value of the lac attribute is NOT 0.

The Routing Area Code of a routing area. The value -1 of the attribute is used to mark that the optional RAC IE should NOT be sent in the Target ID IE of the HANDOVER REQUIRED S1 message. Refer to 3GPP TS 36.413.
Indicates whether the MO has been last modified by the Automated Neighbor Relations (ANR) function or operator.
The date and time when the MO was last modified by the Automated Neighbor Relations (ANR) function or operator. Format: YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM:SS
Indicates the time and date when the MO was created by the Automated Neighbor Relations (ANR) function or operator. Format: "YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM:SS"
The identity of the UtranCell represented by this MO, particularly for automatically created ExternalUtranCell managed objects. The masterUtranCellId is set to the Full Distinguished Name (FDN).
Indicates whether the MO has been created by the Automated Neighbor Relations (ANR) function or operator.
The value component of the Relative Distinguished Name (RDN).
Indicates the physical layer identity of the cell, that is, the primary scrambling code.
UTRAN Cell Identity. Used to identity the cell uniquely within UTRAN Iu mode.
PLMN ID supported by the cell.
Contains a list of MO instances that reserve this MO instance.
Label for free use.

This parameter indicates if the external UTRAN cell is RIM capable. If the value is RIMIncapable, no attempt will be made to create a RIM association to the external UTRAN cell, other values will result in a attempt to create a RIM association.
This parameter indicates the current status of the RIM association to this external cell.

It is strongly recommended to only set the attributes that correspond to a desired functionality and leave all other temporary attributes set to default value. Information in the descriptions about what attributes are in use may be overridden by the information in CPI Info documents. Note that a later release may use another attribute to control the functionality previously provided by a temporary attribute, or may remove the functionality altogether. In these cases, the change is documented in the NIR.

Indicates if the Automated Neighbor Relations (ANR) function is allowed to remove this object. It does not restrict operator removal of the object. Objects created by ANR have this parameter set to true initially.
